# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if the platform is not standard, it may be better to ignore it.
#Lockfile should be in git, so we do not ignore it.

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock should be committed

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock should be committed
.pdm-python
.pdm-build/

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/lincolnloop/layman and github.com/pdm-project/pdm
